messages.message:
Cypress test status going into tomorrow:
• aihub-redigitization, aihub-single-classification, and aihub-split-classification were fixed by Paul
• converse-app has a PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/57105) up but is still flaky even with the change @Aayush 
• aihub-data-types is flaky and failing on most PR branches @CJ 
• billing tests are flaky because of a backend race condition, I have something I want to try tomorrow and if that doesn't work we might have to skip them until we migrate to metronome
• loginless-sample-results is fixed
• view-my-hub route checks are fixed; need to keep an eye on one that I saw a 403 error in
Let's keep an eye on the next deployment of master, but I think we're close!

@danny.lan we just saw a failure of aihub-quick-clean-refinement because of a 500 model error during extraction: https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/9538/overview/46876036-d325-489b-98eb-b310bba6e4c2/replay?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1
I wonder if we can add some sort of retry mechanism for extraction if this is somewhat common. I recently removed default retries for react-query if it's a 500 error, but there are probably queries like this that should be an exception

Also @danny.lan because I see you worked on `deleteProjectIfItExists` most recently - we had an error of aihub-redigitzation here (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/9538/overview/2a8587ff-1e0c-4396-a943-d47566c75268/replay?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1715224324628.7&att=1) because a project failed to delete. Really odd error, 500 "An unexpected error has occured: Unknown exception"
